response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Unique Characters\", \"description\": \"Given a string, write a function that returns the number of unique characters in it.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef count_unique_chars(s: str) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing any characters.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the number of unique characters in the input string.\", \"code\": \"def count_unique_chars(s: str) -> int:\\n    return len(set(s))\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert count_unique_chars(\\\"abc\\\") == 3\", \"assert count_unique_chars(\\\"aabbcc\\\") == 3\", \"assert count_unique_chars(\\\"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\\\") == 26\", \"assert count_unique_chars(\\\"\\\") == 0\"] }"
